studyDesigns.name: Study Design
studyDesigns.rationale: Protocol-defined study design for investigating efficacy and safety

arms.name: Arm A: Avelumab + Axitinib
arms.description: Avelumab 10 mg/kg IV Q2W in a 6-week cycle + axitinib 5 mg PO BID continuously. Intrapatient axitinib dose escalation may occur if relevant criteria are met.

arms.name: Arm B: Sunitinib
arms.description: Sunitinib 50 mg PO QD on Schedule 4/2 (4 weeks on treatment followed by 2 weeks off) in 6-week cycles.

studyCohorts.characteristic: Patients with PD-L1 expression prospectively defined as positive

maskingRoles.text: This is an Open Label study with no masking

population.name: Study Population
population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To demonstrate that avelumab in combination with axitinib is superior to sunitinib monotherapy in prolonging PFS or OS in the first-line treatment of PD-L1 positive patients (patient population prospectively defined as noted in Section 7.5.1) with aRCC.

objectives.name: Secondary PFS Objective (Unselected)
objectives.text: To demonstrate that avelumab in combination with axitinib is superior to sunitinib monotherapy in prolonging PFS in the first-line treatment of patients with aRCC unselected for PD-L1 expression.

objectives.name: Secondary OS Objective (Unselected)
objectives.text: To demonstrate that avelumab in combination with axitinib is superior to sunitinib monotherapy in prolonging OS in the first-line treatment of patients with aRCC unselected for PD-L1 expression.

objectives.name: Other Efficacy Measures
objectives.text: To evaluate other measures of efficacy of avelumab in combination with axitinib and sunitinib monotherapy in the first-line treatment of aRCC patients.

objectives.name: Next-line Therapy Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate progression-free survival on next-line of therapy (PFS2).

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the overall safety profile of avelumab in combination with axitinib and sunitinib monotherapy in the first-line treatment of aRCC patients.

objectives.name: Toxicity Discontinuation Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the time to treatment discontinuation/failure due to toxicity.

objectives.name: Toxicity Proportion Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the proportion of patients who discontinued treatment due to toxicity.

objectives.name: Pharmacokinetics Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the population pharmacokinetics of avelumab and axitinib when administered in combination.

objectives.name: Biomarker Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate candidate predictive biomarkers in pre-treatment tumor tissue that may aid in the identification of a patient subpopulation most likely to benefit from treatment with avelumab in combination with axitinib and sunitinib monotherapy.

objectives.name: Immunogenicity Objective
objectives.text: To assess the immunogenicity of avelumab when combined with axitinib.

objectives.name: Patient-Reported Outcomes Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the effects of avelumab in combination with axitinib and sunitinib monotherapy on patient-reported outcomes.

endpoints.name: Primary PFS (PD-L1+)
endpoints.text: Progression-Free Survival (PFS) based on Blinded Independent Central Review (BICR) assessment per RECIST v.1.1 for PD-L1 positive patients (patient population prospectively defined as noted in Section 7.5.1).

endpoints.name: Primary OS (PD-L1+)
endpoints.text: Overall Survival (OS) for PD-L1 positive patients (patient population prospectively defined as noted in Section 7.5.1).

endpoints.name: Secondary PFS (Unselected)
endpoints.text: PFS by BICR assessment per RECIST v.1.1 for patients unselected for PD-L1 expression.

endpoints.name: Secondary OS (Unselected)
endpoints.text: OS for patients unselected for PD-L1 expression.

endpoints.name: Tumor Response Endpoints
endpoints.text: Objective Response (OR), Disease Control (DC), Time to Tumor Response (TTR) and Duration of Response (DR) based on BICR assessment and based on Investigator assessment, per RECIST v.1.1.

endpoints.name: Investigator PFS
endpoints.text: Progression-Free Survival (PFS) based on Investigator assessment per RECIST v.1.1.

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoints
endpoints.text: Adverse events (AEs) and laboratory abnormalities as graded by National Cancer Institute (NCI) Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events (CTCAE) v4.03 (Appendix 6); vital signs (blood pressure, pulse rate).

endpoints.name: Time to Discontinuation
endpoints.text: Time to treatment discontinuation/failure due to toxicity.

endpoints.name: PK Parameters
endpoints.text: PK parameters including trough concentrations (Ctrough) of avelumab and trough concentrations (Ctrough) and maximum concentrations (Cmax) of axitinib.

endpoints.name: Biomarker Status
endpoints.text: Tumor tissue biomarker status (ie, positive or negative; based on, for example, PD-L1 expression and/or quantitation of tumor infiltrating CD8+ T lymphocytes as assessed by immunohistochemistry [IHC]).

endpoints.name: Biomarker Subgroup Outcomes
endpoints.text: Measures of clinical outcome (PFS, OS, OR, DC, TTR, and DR) in biomarker-positive and biomarker-negative subgroups.

endpoints.name: Immunogenicity Endpoint
endpoints.text: Anti-drug antibodies (ADAs; nAbs) of avelumab when in combination with axitinib.

endpoints.name: PRO Endpoints
endpoints.text: Patient-Reported Outcomes (PRO): FACT-Kidney Symptom Index (FKSI-19), EuroQol 5-Dimension (EQ 5D).

notes.text: 1. Visit Identifiers: All assessments should be performed prior to dosing with study treatments unless otherwise indicated.
2. Informed Consent: Must be obtained prior to undergoing any study-specific procedure.
3. Medical/Oncological History: To include information on prior systemic adjuvant or neoadjuvant therapy regimens, surgery, and radiation therapy.
4. Baseline Signs/Symptoms: To be recorded pre-dose on Cycle 1 Day 1.
5. Physical Examination: Includes an examination of major body systems and weight.

6. Contraception Check: Male patients with female partner of childbearing potential and female patients who are of childbearing potential will need to affirm that they meet the criteria for correct use of contraception.
14. Tumor Assessments: CT or MRI will include chest, abdomen and pelvis (CAP) at all time points.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) will include all patients who are randomized to study treatment. Patients will be analyzed according to the treatment arm to which they were randomized.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) will include all patients who are randomized to study treatment. Patients will be analyzed according to the treatment arm to which they were randomized.

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The safety analysis set will include all patients who receive at least one dose of study treatment. Patients will be analyzed according to the treatment they actually received.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The safety analysis set will include all patients who receive at least one dose of study treatment. Patients will be analyzed according to the treatment they actually received.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received at least one dose of study treatment

analysisPopulations.name: Per-protocol analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: The per-protocol (PP) analysis set is a subset of the FAS and will include all patients who do not have any major protocol deviations that would impact the efficacy evaluation.
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The per-protocol (PP) analysis set is a subset of the FAS and will include all patients who do not have any major protocol deviations that would impact the efficacy evaluation.
analysisPopulations.criteria: FAS subset AND no major protocol deviations

analysisPopulations.name: PK analysis sets
analysisPopulations.text: The PK analysis set will include all patients who are randomized and receive at least one dose of avelumab or axitinib and have at least one measurable concentration of avelumab or axitinib.
analysisPopulations.label: PKAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The PK analysis set will include all patients who are randomized and receive at least one dose of avelumab or axitinib and have at least one measurable concentration of avelumab or axitinib.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose AND >=1 measurable concentration

analysisPopulations.name: Biomarker analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: The biomarker analysis set will include all patients who are randomized and have at least one baseline biomarker assessment.
analysisPopulations.label: BAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The biomarker analysis set will include all patients who are randomized and have at least one baseline biomarker assessment.

analysisPopulations.name: Immunogenicity analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: The immunogenicity analysis set will include all patients who are randomized and receive at least one dose of avelumab and have at least one valid ADA assessment after the first dose of avelumab.
analysisPopulations.label: IAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The immunogenicity analysis set will include all patients who are randomized and receive at least one dose of avelumab and have at least one valid ADA assessment after the first dose of avelumab.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose avelumab AND >=1 post-dose ADA assessment

analysisPopulations.name: PRO analysis set
analysisPopulations.text: The PRO analysis set will include all patients who are randomized, receive at least one dose of study treatment, and have at least one PRO assessment (at baseline or post-baseline).
analysisPopulations.label: PROAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The PRO analysis set will include all patients who are randomized, receive at least one dose of study treatment, and have at least one PRO assessment (at baseline or post-baseline).
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose AND >=1 PRO assessment

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Advanced Renal Cell Carcinoma
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Patients with advanced renal cell carcinoma (aRCC).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: First-line Treatment
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: First-line treatment of patients with advanced renal cell carcinoma.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: ECOG Performance Status
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group Performance Status (ECOG PS) of 0 or 1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Prior Systemic Therapy Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Patients must not have received prior systemic therapy for advanced renal cell carcinoma.

studyInterventions.name: Avelumab
studyInterventions.description: Fully human monoclonal antibody (mAb) of the immunoglobulin (Ig) G1 isotype that selectively binds to PD-L1.

studyInterventions.name: Axitinib
studyInterventions.description: Oral, small molecule, tyrosine kinase inhibitor (TKI) selective for VEGFRs 1, 2, and 3.

studyInterventions.name: Sunitinib
studyInterventions.description: Oral, multitargeted TKI of KIT, PDGFRs, VEGFRs, RET, and FLT3; used as monotherapy in the control arm.

studyInterventions.name: Anti-emetic treatment
studyInterventions.description: Permitted supportive care for prophylaxis or treatment of nausea/vomiting.

studyInterventions.name: CYP3A4/5 Inhibitors and Inducers
studyInterventions.description: Medications that may interact with axitinib or sunitinib metabolism.

conditions.name: Response Confirmation
conditions.description: Requirement for confirming CR or PR
conditions.text: CR and PR must be confirmed with repeated imaging performed at least 4 weeks after initial documentation of response.

conditions.name: PD Confirmation
conditions.text: If radiologic imaging shows progressive disease (PD), then tumor assessment should be repeated after at least 4 weeks to confirm PD.

conditions.name: Avelumab Re-treatment Eligibility
conditions.description: Criteria for re-treating with avelumab after PD
conditions.text: 1) No cancer treatment other than axitinib since last avelumab dose, 2) patient does not meet safety withdrawal criteria, 3) trial is still open.

study.name: A PHASE 3, MULTINATIONAL, RANDOMIZED, OPEN-LABEL, PARALLEL-ARM STUDY OF AVELUMAB (MSB0010718C) IN COMBINATION WITH AXITINIB (INLYTA) VERSUS SUNITINIB (SUTENT) MONOTHERAPY IN THE FIRST-LINE TREATMENT OF PATIENTS WITH ADVANCED RENAL CELL CARCINOMA

administrations.name: Arm A: Avelumab regimen
administrations.duration: Until disease progression, unacceptable toxicity, or withdrawal

administrations.name: Arm B: Sunitinib regimen
administrations.duration: 4 weeks on, 2 weeks off (Schedule 4/2) in 6-week cycles

studyDefinitionDocument.name: A Phase 3, Multinational, Randomized, Open-Label Study to Evaluate Efficacy and Safety of Avelumab (MSB0010718C) in Combination with Axitinib Versus Sunitinib Monotherapy as First-Line Treatment in Patients with Advanced Renal Cell Carcinoma

transitionRules.name: Screening to Randomization
transitionRules.text: Subject must meet all inclusion/exclusion criteria and provide informed consent.

transitionRules.name: Dose Modification for Toxicity
transitionRules.text: Axitinib and Sunitinib treatment may be adjusted by dosing interruption with or without dose reduction for investigational product-related toxicity.

transitionRules.name: Single Agent Continuation
transitionRules.text: Patients in Arm A who stop one of the two study drugs for reasons other than PD may continue on single agent treatment with the other drug.

commentAnnotations.text: Visit Identifiers: All assessments should be performed prior to dosing with study treatments unless otherwise indicated.
Home Blood Pressure Monitoring: Patients should be instructed to contact the site immediately if systolic BP > 150 mm Hg or diastolic BP > 100 mm Hg.
irRECIST-defined antitumor activity will no longer be collected as per PACL dated 02 September 2019.
Cytology samples (eg, FFPE cell pellet from Fine Needle Aspiration biopsy) are not acceptable.

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Discontinuation of Blinded Independent Central Review (BICR) for disease progression assessment following final PFS analyses.
Discontinuation of irRECIST-defined antitumor activity data collection.
Introduction of a specific laboratory test schedule post IA3 cut-off date.
Updated safety monitoring guidelines for myocarditis including BNP and Troponin.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: Final analyses for PFS have been performed as specified in the protocol, allowing transition to investigator-assessed progression.
Alignment with PACL dated 02 September 2019 regarding irRECIST data collection.
Occurrence of myocarditis cases in early phases of treatment necessitated enhanced cardiac monitoring.
